OL,3,CLess than two-thirds 'very likely' to
OL,4,Creport domestic abuse, survey suggests
OL,6,FResults from the Northern Ireland life
OL,7,Fand times (NILT) survey 2023 show 63%
OL,8,Fof people surveyed would be "very
OL,9,Flikely" to report becoming the victim
OL,10,Fof domestic abuse to police.
OL,12,FThe statistics were lowest for those
OL,13,Faged 18 to 24, with only 45% saying
OL,14,Fthey would be "very likely" to report.
OL,16,FMen were more likely to report being
OL,17,Fvictims of domestic abuse, with 65%
OL,18,Fsaying they were "very likely" to go
OL,19,Fto the police compared to 62% of women
OL,20,Fsurveyed.
